cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper is about a computer vision task of long-term object tracking, which involves developing a framework for tracking an object over a long period of time. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves designing a bounding box regressor and a target verifier, which are machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also involves designing a skimming module to efficiently choose the most possible regions, which involves optimization techniques, making cs.RO (Robotics) another likely category. The paper also involves evaluating the performance of the proposed method on benchmark datasets, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Finally, the paper involves processing image data, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible category.
